Data: Toss: George Bailey has won the toss and Australia will bowl first. They are playing an unchanged team. Hafeez said he too would have bowled first. He says a target of 150 plus on this pitch will be tough to chase.

If Pakistan can sneak in a few early wickets and expose the middle order, we will have a cracker. Join us shortly.

Not a bad score but Pakistan would have been comfortable with so much more in this crucial game. The early wickets dented their plans and as a result at the end of ten overs they progressed at ODI pace, 5.5 an over and thereabouts. Jamshed provided the acceleration and Kamran Akmal gave him good support but Pakistan needed some big overs towards the end ideally.
